summary: Today in the library one of my kids chose a dusty old book called Erik and the Christmas Horse to read to the class. It was set...
body:
Today in the library one of my kids chose a dusty old book called Erik and the Christmas Horse to read to the class. It was set in Gothenburg which had me all like o m g because I lived there for a while and it changed my life.

Thennnn, they referenced St.Lucia’s day, which is on December 13. I explained the holiday to them and kept reading. A few pages later one of them put their hand up and was all like “hey, Taylor Swift’s birthday is on December 13” and then a few pages after that another kid called out “I WORKED OUT TAYLOR SWIFT’S FAVOURITE NUMBER IS 13 BECAUSE IT IS HER BIRTHDAY!” 😂

I love their super relevant connections with the texts we read 😬😬

summary: I want to remember the colour of the sweater, the temperature of the air, the creak of the floorboards, the time on the clock...
caption:
I want to remember the colour of the sweater, the temperature of the air, the creak of the floorboards, the time on the clock when your heart was stolen or shattered or healed or claimed forever.

The fun challenge of writing a pop song is squeezing those evocative details into the catchiest melodic cadence you can possibly think of. I thrive on the challenge of sprinkling personal mementos and shreds of reality into a genre of music that is universally known for being, well, universal.

summary: When I went to Paris in 2016, I walked past these willow trees and I remember thinking. “Taylor sat right there. That’s where...
body: When I went to Paris in 2016, I walked past these willow trees and I remember thinking. “Taylor sat right there. That’s where Taylor sat when she made the begin again music video.” It’s such a surreal experience being in the same spot as your idol, something I have experienced 3 times in real time and a few after she has been there. I thank my lucky stars every day for Taylor swift; she’s helped me through too many things to count. I love you @taylorswift 🦋
